sentence.text: Epidermal growth factor receptor (positive regulation of protein phosphorylation) mutation is prevalently expressed in lung adenocarcinoma cases and acts as one of the major driving oncogenes.

positive regulation of protein phosphorylation tyrosine kinase inhibitors (TKIs) have been used in patients with positive regulation of protein phosphorylation-mutant as an effective targeted therapy in lung adenocarcinoma, but drug resistance and tumor recurrence inevitably occurs.

Recently, transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway-associate protein (regulation of cell cycle) has been reported to promote multiple cancer cell properties, such as promoting cell proliferation, epithelial-mesenchymal transition and drug resistance.
